														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1824472">
									

<p>Official exception. It's a workaround so that the core page (which is the actual SCP being rated) can be rated without double modules (one from the SCP and one from the iteration page it loads) popping up. <a href="/scp-1893">SCP-1893</a> did the same thing. If you take a look at the &quot;Random Page&quot; link, it specifically notes that although a rating module appears, that's an artifact of it pulling the module off the linked page and only rates the actual host page rather than the iteration.</p>
<p>To clarify: if there was a rating module on the separate iterations, they would show up on the core page as well, but only rate that page rather than the iteration pages.</p>

							</div>

